This topic describes how to install <%= vars.platform_name %> Dev on Windows 7 and 8.


## <a id="prerequisites"></a> Prerequisites

These sections describe the prerequisites you must have before installing <%= vars.platform_name %> Dev on Windows 7 and 8.

### <a id="virtualbox"></a> VirtualBox

<%= vars.platform_name %> Dev uses [VirtualBox](https://www.virtualbox.org) v5.0 or later as its virtualizer.

To install VirtualBox:

1. Download VirtualBox v5.0.14 for Windows hosts from [VirtualBox](http://download.virtualbox.org/virtualbox/5.0.14/VirtualBox-5.0.14-105127-Win.exe).

1. Open the `.exe` file and install using the wizard.

### <a id="cf-cli"></a> Cloud Foundry Command Line Interface

<%= vars.platform_name %> Dev uses the Cloud Foundry Command Line Interface (cf CLI) to push and scale apps.

To install the cf CLI:

1. Download the [cf CLI for Windows (64 bit)](https://cli.run.pivotal.io/stable?release=windows64&source=github-rel). If you previously used the cf CLI v5 Ruby gem, uninstall this gem first.

1. Unpack the ZIP file and open the `cf_installer` app.

1. Follow the installer wizard to install.

1. To verify your installation, open a terminal window and enter `cf`. If your installation was successful, the cf CLI help listing appears.


## <a id="install-pcf-dev"></a> Install <%= vars.platform_name %> Dev

To install <%= vars.platform_name %> Dev:

1. Download <%= vars.platform_name %> Dev v0.30 from the [<%= vars.platform_name %> Dev](https://network.pivotal.io/products/pcfdev#/releases/1622) page on Pivotal Network.

1. Unzip the downloaded ZIP file.

1. Using PowerShell, navigate to the directory containing the unzipped plugin file.

1. Install the CF Dev plugin by running:

	```
	.\pcfdev-VERSION-windows.exe
	```

1. Start <%= vars.platform_name %> Dev by running:

	```
	cf dev start
	```
  	It may take several minutes for the <%= vars.platform_name %> Dev virtual machine (VM) and its services to start.
	<p class="note"><strong>Note:</strong> You may be prompted to continue if your available memory is less than the recommended amount.</p>

1. If prompted, enter your API token. This token is required for authentication and appears at the bottom of the **Edit Profile** tab in your Pivotal Network account.
	<p class="note"><strong>Note:</strong> The API token does not appear in the terminal session when you enter it.</p>

After the **<%= vars.platform_name %> Dev is now running** banner appears, you can log in. For more information about logging in, see the [Log In to Your <%= vars.platform_name %> Dev Instance](./usage.html#pcf-dev) section of the _Using <%= vars.platform_name %> Dev_ topic.


## <a id="stopping"></a> Stop <%= vars.platform_name %> Dev

To temporarily stop <%= vars.platform_name %> Dev:

1. Navigate to your app directory.

1. Run:

	```
	cf dev stop
	```


## <a id="uninstall"></a> Uninstall <%= vars.platform_name %> Dev

To destroy the <%= vars.platform_name %> Dev VM:

1. Navigate to your app directory.

1. Run:

	```
	cf dev destroy
	```

To remove the <%= vars.platform_name %> Dev:

1. Run:

	```
	cf uninstall-plugin pcfdev
	```
